<dl id="n03118e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03118e">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03118e"> 118(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> put me wise <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n03118e"><li>FW 31.07 </li><li><a href="../../flex/b/lexb.htm#n03118e">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/b/l39b.htm#n03118e">1939</a> &nbsp;<a href="../../flex/z/lexfh.htm#n03118e">FH IX</a> </li><li><ms href="#n03118e">MS BL 47472-98</ms> </li><li>JJA 45:005 <a name="b11d" href="../../FF/fdra/bda.htm#b11d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/b/b11d.htm#n03118e">Draft: I.2&sect;1.1</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;&hellip; Den he&apos;s goin&apos; to shoot snow-birds in de Klondike. He says yer told him not to send &apos;round no more pink notes nor come hanglin&apos; over de garden gate, and he takes dis means of <mark>puttin&apos; yer wise</mark> &hellip;&rdquo; <small> O. Henry, <a name="OHFM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#OHFM"><cite title="source">The Four Million</cite></a> (1906) [&lsquo;By Courier&rdquo;] 234</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: The speaker is delivering a garbled version of a message given on the previous page by a young man threatening to join an Alaska moose-hunting expedition. </mm> </dd></dl>
